# Keep dev-only repo files OUT of the packaged `.plugin`. `git archive` honors
# `export-ignore`, so the standard build command (see BUILD.md) produces a clean,
# installable plugin with no extra steps.
#
# Why: Claude Desktop's plugin validator runs in STRICT mode (warnings = errors). A
# `CLAUDE.md` at the plugin root raises a warning ("not loaded as project context"),
# and strict mode turns that into a hard "Plugin validation failed" — which blocked
# the v0.5.0 upload. These files are developer docs for the source repo and are never
# loaded at runtime, so excluding them from the package costs nothing functionally.
CLAUDE.md      export-ignore
BUILD.md       export-ignore
.gitattributes export-ignore
